# Stylelint and Less Styling Standards

> **Related Rules**: See [Theme Customization](./theming.mdc), [Git Workflow](./git-workflow.mdc)

## Basic Principles

- All Less files must pass Stylelint checks
- Use Less as CSS preprocessor
- Follow BEM naming convention (if applicable)
- Keep style code clean and maintainable

## Execution Methods

```bash
# Check all style files
yarn lint:style

# Check specific files
npx stylelint 'src/**/*.less'
```

## Configuration Requirements

- Use `stylelint-config-standard` as base configuration
- Use `stylelint-config-clean-order` to standardize property order
- Use `stylelint-declaration-block-no-ignored-properties` to detect invalid properties

## Less Usage Standards

- Use variables to define colors, fonts, spacing, etc.
- Use nesting to keep style hierarchy clear
- Use Mixins to reuse style code
- Avoid excessive nesting (recommended max 3 levels)

## Style Organization

- Organize style properties in logical order
- Use property order standardized by `stylelint-config-clean-order`
- Group related style properties

## ng-alain Theme Integration

- Use ng-alain theme variables
- Follow ng-alain theme customization standards (see [Theme Customization Standards](./theming.mdc))
- Refer to theme-related documentation in `docs/`

## Git Hooks Integration

- Automatically check styles before commit through `lint-staged` (see [Git Workflow](./git-workflow.mdc))
- Only check modified style files

